public interface ArrayTypeDeclarator
extends PrimaryExpression

This PrimaryExpression type represents an array type declarator.

An array type declarator is something like 

      AnyType[][][...
i.e. a type identifier, including qualified type identifiers and primitive types, followed by one ore more '[]' character sequences.

Important note: There's no explicit grammar rule for array type declarators with the grammar used by the JSourceObjectizer. However, this class collects the array's type and all array declarators, i.e. all pairs of opening/closing square brackets. As a result, if using the JSourceMmarshaller on an instance of this class the marshaller will just return a string representing the most right opening/closing square brackets.
